DataType

Primitive DataType
Byte, Short, int ,long, float, double, char, boolean,

Non Primitive DataType
String literal, String object

Primitive datatype conversion;
Widening casting (automatically)--small to large;
narrowing casting (manually)---large to small;

Primitive and Non-Primitive conversion
String (Numeric String )
Integer.parseInt(Numeric String); NumberFormatException
Double.parseDouble(Numeric String)
Integer.valueOf(String)----returnType---Object;
Convert primitive types to String: String.valueOf();

Common method of string
indexOff(), length(), replace(), charAt

Java operators:
Arithmetic operators: +, -, *, /, %, ++, --;
Assignment operators: =, +=, x+=5; x=x+5;
Comparison Operators: <, >, ==, <=, >=, !=;
Logical Operators: &&, ||, !;
Bitwise Operators: &, |;
Console Input: argument,Scanner Object;

Package Java Project as a jar file:mvn package;

Condition statement:
if
if else
Nested if
switch case
ternary ? :




